The paper deals with game theory and computation, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) as the primary sub-category. However, the paper also discusses the relationship between game theory and cryptography, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of computation in games, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the conditions under which equilibria exist, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
